 The event was celebrated by a full parade in MOTH regalia at the Gondar Shellhole where a drone also captured the special arrival. The vehicle belongs to Mr Monty Truwig who bought it for R15 000 in 2010.
Mr Struwig bought it to sell as scrap metal when steel prices were between R5 and R6 per kilogram. Also read: Gondar Shellhole gasheer vir MOTH’s se 90 ste He however did a little research on the vehicle and decided not to cut it up and sell it, but rather to donate it to the MOTH’s where the Saracen have found a honorary spot in front of the Shellhole. A bottle of champagne was broken on the Saracen to mark the special occasion.    Sangoma on murder charge Kake van lewe by brandweer gesteel Helikopterritte by Buiteleweskou Major General among N4 road casualties   • Save our standby number (072 248 3855) and send us a WhatsApp message with the words “Add me” to be added to our broadcast list. • Like us on Facebook, follow us on Twitter and Instagram. • Subscribe to our YouTube channel. Contact our news room on our 24 hr standby number 072 248 3855, or send a mail to our editor tobie@mobserver.co.za Click here to subscribe to a bi-weekly newsletter of local, national and international news